    "in a parallel forms setting, which the authors often derive themselves.",
    "To account for the in-and output modalities of their artificial test subjects, authors adapted original tests, e.g.",
    "by expressing interactive experiments in textbased stories.",
    "And finally, to evade the problem of training data contamination with test material, several papers chose to rephrase tests.",
    "Any modification of test items requires a re-validation of the changed material including empirical or logical evidence."
